# GitHub Actions – Configure Self-Hosted Runner on Linux

A Self-Hosted Runner on Linux allows GitHub Actions workflows to run on your own Linux machine instead of GitHub-hosted virtual machines.

This is commonly used for:

* Enterprise CI/CD
* Internal deployments
* GPU workloads
* Kubernetes deployments
* Custom software environments
* Persistent build systems

---

# What is a Linux Self-Hosted Runner?

A Linux self-hosted runner is:

> A Linux machine connected to GitHub Actions for executing workflow jobs.

The Linux machine can be:

* Ubuntu server
* CentOS server
* Debian VM
* Cloud VM
* Local Linux machine
* Docker container

---

# Workflow Architecture

```text id="jlwmra"
Developer Pushes Code
          ↓
GitHub Actions Triggered
          ↓
Linux Self-Hosted Runner Receives Job
          ↓
Workflow Executes on Linux Machine
          ↓
Results Sent Back to GitHub
```

