# Real-World Enterprise Example

---

# Scenario

Company deploys application to private Kubernetes cluster.

GitHub-hosted runners cannot access internal network.

Use Linux self-hosted runner.

---

# Workflow

```yaml id="jlwmr3"
name: Internal Kubernetes Deployment

on:
  push:
    branches:
      - main

jobs:
  deploy:
    runs-on:
      - self-hosted
      - linux
      - production

    steps:
      - name: Checkout Code
        uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Install Dependencies
        run: npm install

      - name: Build Application
        run: npm run build

      - name: Deploy to Kubernetes
        run: kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml
```

